#      
src = './data_3000/'
img_size = 56       #  
channels = 1
noise_dim = 100
# 
def img_read(src,file):
    img = cv.imread(src+file,cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    return img
def get_data():
    #src     . 
    files = os.listdir(src)
    X = []  

    #      
    #  255  0~1   X  . 

    for file in files:
      
        X.append((img_read(src,file)-127.5)/127.5) 
    

    # Train set(80%), Test set(20%)  
    X_train, X_test = train_test_split(X, test_size=0.2, random_state=1,shuffle=True)
        
    # (x, 56, 56, 1)   
    X_train = np.expand_dims(X_train, axis=3)
    X_test = np.expand_dims(X_test, axis=3)


    return X_train, X_test

#    (  y   )
X_train, X_test = get_data()
print("X_train.shape = {}".format(X_train.shape))
print("X_test.shape = {}".format(X_test.shape))

X_train.shape = (2400, 56, 56, 1)
X_test.shape = (600, 56, 56, 1)

4. 모델링 및 학습¶

Generator network 구성¶

In [0]:
# ---------------------
#  Generator   (input : noise / output : image)
# ---------------------    
 
def build_generator():
    model = Sequential()
   
    model.add(layers.Dense(256, use_bias=False, input_shape=(100,)))
    model.add(layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
    model.add(layers.BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
    model.add(layers.Dense(512))
    model.add(layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
    model.add(layers.BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
    model.add(layers.Dense(1024))
    model.add(layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
    model.add(layers.BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
    model.add(layers.Dense(np.prod(56*56), activation='tanh'))
    model.add(layers.Reshape((56,56,1)))
    # noise  , model noise   
    noise = Input(shape=(100,))
    img = model(noise)
    model.summary()
    return Model(noise,img)

optimizer = Adam(0.0002, 0.5)

generated_image = generator(noise, training=False)
plt.imshow(generated_image[0, :, :, 0], cmap='gray')

Discriminator network 구성¶

In [0]:
# ---------------------
#  Discriminator   (input : image / output : (0 1 ))
# ---------------------   
def build_discriminator():
    model = tf.keras.Sequential()
    img_shape = (img_size, img_size, channels)
    model.add(layers.Flatten(input_shape=img_shape))
    model.add(layers.Dense(512))
    model.add(layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
    
    model.add(layers.Dense(256))
    model.add(layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
    model.add(layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
    
    model.summary()
    #    , model   
    img = Input(shape=img_shape)
    validity = model(img)
        
    return Model(img, validity)

discriminator 모델 생성과 컴파일¶

# image discriminator     (. )
decision = discriminator(generated_image)

Combined Model 구성¶

  • noise -> generator -> discriminator
In [0]:
# Combined Model
#        generator  discriminator . 

z = layers.Input(shape=(100,), name="noise_input")
img = generator(z)

#       discriminator  .  generator 
discriminator.trainable = False

# discriminator      
valid = discriminator(img)

# generator discriminator  . (     )
# discriminator  generator 
combined = Model(z, valid)
combined.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer)
combined.summary()

Training 함수¶

In [0]:
def train(epochs, batch_size=128, sample_interval=50):
              
        #    . valid 1, fake 0
        valid = np.ones((batch_size, 1))
        fake = np.zeros((batch_size, 1))
        history = []
        for epoch in range(epochs):
            
            # ---------------------
            #  Train Discriminator
            # ---------------------
            
            # batch_size    
            idx = np.random.randint(0, X_train.shape[0], batch_size)
            imgs = X_train[idx]
            
            # Sample noise (batch_size)
            noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (batch_size, 100))
            
            # noise generator  fake image  
            gen_imgs = generator.predict(noise)
            
            # discriminator .   1 ,   0 
            # discriminator    valid fake 
            #    binary_crossentropy  .
            d_loss_real = discriminator.train_on_batch(imgs, valid)
            d_loss_fake = discriminator.train_on_batch(gen_imgs, fake)
            
            # real   fake   discriminator loss accracy  .
            d_loss = 0.5 * np.add(d_loss_real, d_loss_fake)
            
            # ---------------------
            #  Train Generator
            # ---------------------
            
            # noise 
            noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (batch_size, noise_dim))
            
            # noise  discriminator real image  generator 
            g_loss = combined.train_on_batch(noise, valid)

            history.append({"D":d_loss[0],"G":g_loss})

            # sample_interval(1000) epoch  loss accuracy  
            if epoch % sample_interval == 0:
                print("%d [D loss: %f, acc.: %.2f%%] [G loss: %f]" % (epoch, d_loss[0], 100*d_loss[1], g_loss))
                sample_images(epoch)
        return(history)
In [0]:
 #  
def sample_images(epoch):
        r, c = 4, 4
        noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (r * c, noise_dim))
        gen_imgs = generator.predict(noise)

        # Rescale images 0 - 1
        gen_imgs = 0.5 * gen_imgs + 0.5

        fig, axs = plt.subplots(r, c)
        cnt = 0
        for i in range(r):
            for j in range(c):
                axs[i,j].imshow(gen_imgs[cnt, :,:,0], cmap=plt.cm.bone)
                axs[i,j].axis('off')
                cnt += 1
#             fig.savefig("images/%d.png" % epoch)
#         plt.close()
